activity_state.help:
Status based on activities
Overdue: Due date is already passed
Today: Activity date is today
Planned: Future activities.

activity_exception_decoration.help: Type of the exception activity on record.

activity_exception_icon.help: Icon to indicate an exception activity.

message_needaction.help: If checked, new messages require your attention.

message_has_error.help: If checked, some messages have a delivery error.

message_has_error_counter.help: Number of messages with delivery error

message_has_sms_error.help: If checked, some messages have a delivery error.

backorder_id.help: If this shipment was split, then this field links to the shipment which contains the already processed part.

return_id.help: If this picking was created as a return of another picking, this field links to the original picking.

move_type.help: It specifies goods to be deliver partially or all at once

state.help:
* Draft: The transfer is not confirmed yet. Reservation doesn't apply.
 * Waiting another operation: This transfer is waiting for another operation before being ready.
 * Waiting: The transfer is waiting for the availability of some products.
(a) The shipping policy is "As soon as possible": no product could be reserved.
(b) The shipping policy is "When all products are ready": not all the products could be reserved.
 * Ready: The transfer is ready to be processed.
(a) The shipping policy is "As soon as possible": at least one product has been reserved.
(b) The shipping policy is "When all products are ready": all product have been reserved.
 * Done: The transfer has been processed.
 * Cancelled: The transfer has been cancelled.

priority.help: Products will be reserved first for the transfers with the highest priorities.

scheduled_date.help: Scheduled time for the first part of the shipment to be processed. Setting manually a value here would set it as expected date for all the stock moves.

date_deadline.help: Date Promise to the customer on the top level document (SO/PO)

has_deadline_issue.help: Is late or will be late depending on the deadline and scheduled date

date.help: Creation Date, usually the time of the order

date_done.help: Date at which the transfer has been processed or cancelled.

json_popover.string: JSON data for the popover widget

picking_type_entire_packs.help: If ticked, you will be able to select entire packages to move

use_create_lots.help: If this is checked only, it will suppose you want to create new Lots/Serial Numbers, so you can provide them in a text field.

use_existing_lots.help: If this is checked, you will be able to choose the Lots/Serial Numbers. You can also decide to not put lots in this operation type.  This means it will create stock with no lot or not put a restriction on the lot taken.

move_line_exist.help: Check the existence of pack operation on the picking

has_packages.help: Check the existence of destination packages on move lines

show_check_availability.help: Technical field used to compute whether the button "Check Availability" should be displayed.

show_allocation.help: Technical Field used to decide whether the button "Allocation" should be displayed.

owner_id.help: When validating the transfer, the products will be assigned to this owner.

is_locked.help: When the picking is not done this allows changing the initial demand. When the picking is done this allows changing the done quantities.

show_operations.help: If this checkbox is ticked, the pickings lines will represent detailed stock operations. If not, the picking lines will represent an aggregate of detailed stock operations.

show_reserved.help: If this checkbox is ticked, Odoo will automatically pre-fill the detailed operations with the corresponding products, locations and lot/serial numbers. For moves that are returns, the detailed operations will always be prefilled, regardless of this option.

products_availability.help: Latest product availability status of the picking

country_code.help:
The ISO country code in two chars. 
You can use this field for quick search.

l10n_cl_sii_barcode.help: This XML contains the portion of the DTE XML that should be coded in PDF417 and printed in the invoice barcode should be present in the printed invoice report to be valid

l10n_cl_dte_status.help:
Status of sending the DTE to the SII:
            - Not sent: the DTE has not been sent to SII but it has created.
            - Ask For Status: The DTE is asking for its status to the SII.
            - Accepted: The DTE has been accepted by SII.
            - Accepted With Objections: The DTE has been accepted with objections by SII.
            - Rejected: The DTE has been rejected by SII.
            - Cancelled: The DTE has been deleted by the user.
            - Manual: The DTE is sent manually, i.e.: the DTE will not be sending manually.

l10n_cl_dte_partner_status.help:
Status of sending the DTE to the partner:
            - Not sent: the DTE has not been sent to the partner but it has sent to SII.
            - Sent: The DTE has been sent to the partner.
